# Trivy ignore file — R17.
#
# Add named CVE/finding IDs here ONLY when there is no upstream fix and the
# risk is formally accepted.  Each entry must include:
#   1. The finding ID (CVE-YYYY-NNNNN or Trivy check ID).
#   2. A dated comment with the reason and re-review date.
#   3. A reference issue / ticket where the deferral was approved.
#
# Example (do not uncomment without a real acceptance decision):
#   CVE-2024-12345  # python:3.12-slim base — no fix as of 2025-06-16; low
#                   # exploitability in containerised runtime; revisit 2025-09.
#                   # Tracked: https://github.com/org/resto/issues/NNN
#
# NEVER add entries without justification; never add wildcards or ecosystem-
# wide ignores.  The goal is zero entries here through timely patching.
